.TH git-uptodate 1 "November 2025" "git-uptodate"
.SH NAME
git-uptodate \- print branch, stash, and working tree status for one or more repositories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-uptodate
.RI [ directory ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-uptodate
prints local repository status including tracked and untracked changes,
stashes, and branch divergence for every Git repository found in the
specified directories. Before reporting ahead/behind counts it runs
.B git remote update --prune
to ensure fresh upstream information. When no directories are supplied the
current working directory is scanned.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I directory
One or more directories to scan recursively for Git repositories. If none
are given the current directory is used.
.TP
.B -h , --help
Show usage information.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns zero on success, non-zero if an error occurs.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B git-uptodate
Scan the current directory.
.TP
.B git-uptodate ~/src
Scan all repositories under \fI~/src\fP.
.TP
.B git uptodate
Invoke as a \fBgit\fP subcommand.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1)
